  "title": "Meta Q4 2025 Earnings Call",
  "datetime": "2026-01-29T21:00:00Z",
  "period": "CY2025_Q4",
  "location": "Menlo Park, CA",
  "url": "https://investor.fb.com/",
  "turns": [
    {
      "speaker_id": "mark-zuckerberg",
      "speaker_name": "Mark Zuckerberg",
      "speaker_role": "CEO",
      "timestamp": "00:01:00",
      "text": "2025 was our best year ever. Full-year revenue was $186.1 billion, up 19%. Meta AI ended the year with 1.82 billion monthly active users — not quite the 2 billion target we set mid-year, but still a remarkable growth trajectory. We announced Orion AR glasses pricing at $999 for developers in December, with consumer availability in Q3 2026. Full-year capex was $65.2 billion, in line with our raised guidance."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "susan-li",
      "speaker_name": "Susan Li",
      "speaker_role": "CFO",
      "timestamp": "00:18:00",
      "text": "Q4 revenue was $57.8 billion, up 21% year-over-year. Full-year operating margin was 43.8%. We generated $62.4 billion in free cash flow for the year. For 2026, we expect capex of $70–80 billion as we continue scaling AI infrastructure. Q1 2026 revenue guidance is $39.5–41.8 billion."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "operator",
      "speaker_name": "Operator",
      "speaker_role": "Operator",
      "timestamp": "00:38:00",
      "text": "Our next question comes from Eric Sheridan at Goldman Sachs."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "analyst-eric-sheridan",
      "speaker_name": "Eric Sheridan",
      "speaker_role": "Analyst",
      "timestamp": "00:38:20",
      "text": "Mark, Orion at $999 for developers — does the consumer pricing in Q3 2026 assume a significant further cost reduction, and what's the supply chain confidence level?"
    }
  ],
